The start of school ‚Äì September 8 - is around the corner! To help parents and students prepare for the return to school, we are hosting four parent meetings to answer your questions.

The online parent meetings are organized by grade level and learning method that you selected for your student(s). The virtual meetings will be broadcast LIVE via ZOOM. The ZOOM link to join each meeting will be published on the CISD website at cisd.org. All of the meetings will be recorded and posted on our website in both English and Spanish to be viewed at any time.

We are happy to take your questions now and will incorporate them into the presentation. Please email info@cisd.org.

#CorsicanaISD #TCC

The deadline to apply for P-EBT food benefits has been extended to August 21. Eligible families can apply for this one-time food benefit. Children who received free or reduced-price school meals through the National School Lunch Program during the 2019-2020 school year are eligible for P-EBT. Eligible families that received SNAP benefits for March have already received P-EBT benefits and do not have to apply. If you did not receive an application link or if you need help filling out the P-EBT application, please contact the P-EBT Call Center at 833-613-6220.

#CorsicanaISD

post_text:
Tonight, the CISD Board voted to delay the start of school until Sept. 8 for all instruction. Several reasons for the delay were discussed citing student and staff safety as the most important. Other factors such as additional time for teachers to train and prepare, campuses to implement new safety features, technology staff to prepare devices, and time to develop parent resources were also discussed. The calendar committee will reconvene to develop options for the remainder of the 2020-2021 academic year.

Student meal services will begin before school starts. More information on the meal program will be available in the next few days. #CorsicanaISD

post_text: Do you know the symptoms of COVID-19? They can range from mild to severe but often include fever, a dry cough, shortness of breath, loss of taste or smell, chills, a sore throat and muscle pain. If you experience any of these symptoms, please call a doctor before leaving home. If you begin feeling ill at work or school, please notify a supervisor and make plans to leave. #WeCanWeWillWeMust #TCC #StaySafeCorsica

post_text:
The CISD Board of Trustees approved an electronic device lease agreement that will maximize the District‚Äôs current technology inventory to provide every student with a device for learning.

‚ÄúThis has been our goal to become a one-to-one district [one device to each student],‚Äù said Superintendent Dr. Diane Frost.

Each year, CISD increases the inventory of computers for both students and teachers. ‚ÄúSince the COVID-19 pandemic began, we quickly realized that electronic delivery of instruction would be imperative for our students,‚Äù said Frost.

The approved lease includes 1935 student laptops, 420 teacher laptops and 264 iPads for pre-kinder students. The annual lease payment will be $378,892.

Corsicana ISD will provide three options to parents/students to receive instruction this fall. One option is in-person on campus, and the other two are virtual online opportunities.

‚ÄúEvery student deserves access to technology. I am very proud and thankful that we can make this happen for our students and teachers,‚Äù said Frost. #CorsicanaISD #OnetoOneDistrict #TechnologyforAll

CISD will be providing three different learning options for the 2020-2021 school year. The options that are available to each grade level were established by the Texas Education Agency.

Option 1: In person learning on campus in a traditional classroom setting (Grades Pre-K through 12) with enhanced, thorough safety and health procedures
Option 2: Virtual At-Home Learning that is scheduled and fully guided by a CISD teacher (Grades 3-12)
Option 3: Virtual Self-Directed learning that occurs each day, but on a schedule set by parents and/or students; CISD teachers will be available for support at scheduled times (Grades Pre-K through 12)

A Student Learning Option Selection Form will be emailed to parents and posted on the website on July 20th. We will be posting updates on our website as our 2020-2021 plans are finalized.

Frequently Asked Questions can be found online: www.cisd.org

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year.
For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Corsicana Daily Sun is at Corsicana High School.
May 22 at 3:49 PM ¬∑ Corsicana, TX ¬∑

WATCH: Corsicana ISD honors teachers of the year

Corsicana Independent School District gave its highest honors to its top two teachers Friday morning at the high school.

The 2020 Golden Apple Secondary Teacher of the Year award went to high school Agriculture teacher Mark Vitters and Rebekah McCallay earned the 2020 Mark Culwell Award for Elementary Teacher of the Year.

Superintendent Dr. Diane Frost surprised the pair with special awards followed by a 'social distancing' parade by friends, fellow faculty members, administrators and CISD police officers.

Read the full story in the Tuesday edition of the Corsicana Daily Sun.

Corsicana Independent School District Superintendent Dr. Diane Frost recently announced several promotions of the district‚Äôs leadership team.

Dr. Elmer Avellaneda was promoted to Associate Superintendent. Shade Boulware was promoted to the Executive Director of Leadership Recruitment and Development in the Human Resources Department. Hal Wasson will take on responsibilities of the CISD Athletic Director in addition to Head Football Coach. Kenya Landers will be the Girls Athletic Coordinator in addition to her Assistant Principal role at Corsicana High School. Greg Davis will be the Boys Athletic Coordinator in addition to his current coaching responsibilities at Corsicana High School.

‚ÄúI am proud to work with these professionals who have proven their dedication and commitment to our students,‚Äù said Frost. ‚ÄúI have confidence in these leaders and their ability to guide our district‚Äôs success.‚Äù #CorsicanaISD @CorsicanaHigh Corsicana High School

post_text: We are delighted to continue the CEF mission with great leadership. #GivingBacktoCISD Congratulations, Candice!
shared_text:
Corsicana Education Foundation
May 8 at 3:19 PM ¬∑

I am very pleased to announce that Candice Ingham has been selected as our new Director of the Corsicana Education Foundation!

Candice has worked with the foundation for the better part of five years. CISD and CEF are very important to her, and she is excited to continue the foundation‚Äôs mission of GIVING BACK TO CISD!!

Candice is a former middle school teacher, and she and her husband, Jon, are both CISD alumni. They have a son, Carter, that attends CMS and three sons, Isaac, Noah and Benjamin, that attend Sam Houston Elementary. They are both involved in our community and have planted their roots here.

Although she is a familiar face to many, please join me in welcoming her as our new Director!

Ellen Sodd, President

Cheerleading tryouts are here! Incoming 7th & 8th grade students will have the opportunity to tryout for cheerleader for the 2020-2021 school year. Please see information and important dates below.

Timeline:
*Interested students must sign up via Google Doc by Friday, May 1, 2020.
*Applications and paperwork will be sent to candidates on May 4 and be due back to ddotson@cisd.org on May 7, 2020.

3.26.2020 CISD Extends School Closure through April 13, 2020 due to the coronavirus pandemic. During the schools closure CISD will continue to offer distance learning opportunities through online instruction as well as paper packets for students.

Students who need paper packets may pick them up, and turn them back in, at any one of the 17 food distribution sites. Breakfast and lunch for the week will be distributed to any CISD student on Mondays and Thursdays from 10am-noon (Collins and Navarro 10am-2pm).

Laptop loans, for CHS students needing a device, will available for check-out on April 1, 2 & 3 at the CHS front entry drive. Please see the distribution schedule for more information. www.cisd.org/coronavirus

post_text:
Update: March 17, 2020

Considering recommendations from federal, state and local health officials Corsicana Independent School District will extend the district closure through April 3, 2020, to control the spread of the coronavirus (COVID-19). We will continue to work with national, state and local health authorities to monitor this situation and evaluate our plans accordingly.

This is a difficult time for everyone in the country including the families, students and staff of our CISD community. We appreciate your words of support and encouragement of our schools as we continue to make difficult decisions regarding this unprecedented situation. Please know that students are at the heart of every decision we make.

The CISD leadership and campus principals have been meeting to determine the best way to continue to provide food and academic learning resources to our students during this extended period. We will continue to update these resources on our website and social media channels, www.cisd.org/coronavirus.

post_text: #CorsicanaISD Experiences in education
shared_text:
Carroll Elementary School
February 27 at 7:22 PM ¬∑

Today, our 3rd and 4th grade students got to take part in an engaging experience right here in our very own town. They have been doing a novel study on the book, Call of the Wild. Today, they got to see the pages come to life right in front of their eyes at Schulman's Movie Bowl Grille - Corsicana. Students were able to depict difference between the movie and book, right away, leaving them blown away at what they read in the book vs. what they saw on the screen. Allowing the students these opportunities not only allows them to become better readers and writers, it is preparing them for STAAR in using these same literature features to compare and contrast different passages provided. This engaging experience was made possible by Randy & Joy Dill and the grant they surprised us with this fall to use on our students at Carroll Elementary. Our teachers and students can‚Äôt say THANK YOU enough for this engaging experience opportunity today! Leah Dill Blackard
